The paper deals with the problem of seed minimization in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-fields such as social networks (cs.SOC), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computational complexity (cs.CC). However, since the paper focuses on developing an algorithmic solution to the problem, and presents a novel algorithm with theoretical guarantees, it is most likely to be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which is a sub-category of CS that deals with the study of social networks and their properties, as well as the development of algorithms and models for analyzing and predicting social phenomena. The other sub-categories listed are also relevant to the paper, but are less likely to be the primary classification since they are broader in scope and cover a wider range of topics.
